First Lady Melania Trump attended the 2017 Invictus Games in Toronto as her first solo overseas trip. The games, founded by Prince Harry, involve wounded armed service members and veterans competing in various sports. Melania Trump met with Prince Harry and Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau during the event. The games began with an emotional speech by Prince Harry, emphasizing the dedication and resilience of the participants. The athletes will compete in events such as wheelchair tennis, powerlifting, sitting volleyball, cycling, and swimming throughout the week. Melania Trump expressed her admiration for the athletes and encouraged them to bring home gold medals.